text:
Michael Lang, an 18-year-old who grew up in a close-knit community in La Grange, Illinois, was ready for the next chapter in his life: college.

But within months, he contracted COVID-19 and died. https://t.co/ASwaMdcedK

name: ABC
text: For decades, doctors have been searching for a surefire way to prevent atrial fibrillation, an abnormal heart rhythm that can prove fatal. Now, a new, high-quality study has ruled out two possible contenders: vitamin D and fish oil supplements. https://t.co/ssGz81HMwk
